cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.DM, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with space-filling curves and their applications in global optimization, database indexing, and dimension reduction. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of space-filling curves using recurrences. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper mentions the computations of space-filling functions and their inverse functions as absolutely convergent geometric series. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with Hamiltonian paths on a discrete grid. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the performance analysis of different space-filling curves in dimension reduction, which could be relevant to control systems.
